							<h4>Search Engines and Meta Search Engines</h4>
							<p><strong>Search Engines</strong></p>	
							<p>If you know what you are searching for, the specific information, the particular phrase, exact name or correct title, you should use a search engine.</p>
							<p>A search engine searches the Web for documents with the key words you entered. It does this by using a program called a "spider"ù to search or "crawl" the Web to find matches for the search terms. It does this extremely quickly. What you see on your screen is a list or index of Web sites and Web addresses that match the search terms. You can look through the list, click on links to Web sites and see what matches best with what you are looking for.</p>
							<p><strong>Commonly used search engines are:</strong></p>

