														<h4>Boolean Search</h4>
							<p>One way to make the searches you perform more efficient and effective is to do Boolean (boo- lee-un) search when you type in the key words or search terms into the search engine or meta search engine.</p>
							<p>What is a Boolean search? Boolean search was named for George Boole (1815-65), a British mathematician who created a system of logic based on algebra that has been used by the computer.</p>
							<p>It is made up of the words, AND, OR, NOT, or NEAR. These words help to narrow or broaden a search. Notice these words are in all capital letters. Not all search engines use the same words or terms, so you must check the search instructions for each search engine to see what words to use. The following table describes the basic functions of each of the words:</p>


